{
  "_comment": "Signals used to detect the user's primary role(s) for the ninite-personalized module. Each signal has a weight; sum weights per role and pick the top-scoring role(s) above a threshold. A user can qualify for multiple roles (e.g. dev + gamer). Signal types: winget (installed via winget list), process (currently running or historical via UserAssist), registry (uninstall key presence), folder (path exists).",
  "_threshold": "Score >= 3 = role active. Ties are OK — multi-role is a normal outcome. If no role scores >= 3, offer only the 'always_useful' bundle.",
  "_matchRule": "Case-insensitive substring match on pattern. For process signals, check both currently-running (Get-Process) and historically-used (UserAssist within last 90 days). For folder signals, existence + at least one file inside.",
